Diagnosis
. Antennal base absent. Several setulae between anterior margin of frons and anterior fronto-orbital seta. Face yellow with median sagittal brownish-yellow to blackish-brown stripe (
Fig. 3
). Occiput brown with median yellow stripe densely white pruinose and submedian stripe of white pruinescence, beginning in posterior margin of eye and fading away posteriorly (
Fig. 2
). Proepisternal lobe with anterodorsal protuberance. Dorsal katepisternum slightly yellow. Katatergite yellow. Vein dm-cu slightly oblique. Coxae yellow (
Fig. 5
). Abdomen with two very wide longitudinal yellow stripes, divided by very narrow brown stripe. Sternite 6 expanded over proximal half to two thirds of epandrium. Outer margin of pregonite with triangular kink on distal third. Surstylus half the length of cercus. Cercus lanceolate (
Fig. 21
).
